-- Regression: REG-02 crash-canary for IRON_HIR_EXPR_HEAP.
--
-- **Motivating Incident.** Phase 37-02's collect_mono_enums_node
-- walker crashed on if/elif/else lowering because of a locally-
-- shadowed struct typedef. Heap-expression dispatch is structurally
-- risky because it lowers to LIR IRON_LIR_HEAP_ALLOC + constructor
-- call, and the emit_c.c HEAP_ALLOC case is precisely the rank-3
-- FIX-01 site where Phase 67-02 added an iron_oom_abort guard on
-- the generated-C malloc path. Walker cases that handle HEAP but
-- fail to recurse into the constructor args silently drop the
-- initializer values, producing a zero-initialized heap object at
-- runtime. Phase 66 added -Werror=switch-enum to catch missing
-- `case IRON_HIR_EXPR_HEAP:` at compile time, and Phase 67-02 added
-- the generated-C OOM guard. This canary is the runtime regression
-- net for the HEAP walker dispatch path.
--
-- **Layout Diagram.** Iron_HeapExpr carries
--   { span, kind, type_ref, constructor_args[], constructor_arg_count }
-- Walker cases that fail to recurse into constructor_args drop the
-- initializer values; cases that ignore type_ref dispatch to the
-- default allocation type (sizeof void*) at codegen time.
-- Complements tests/integration/null_heap_alloc_malloc.iron which
-- is the Phase 67-02 OOM-guard fixture for the same code path.
--
-- **Fix Summary.** Phase 67-08 added this fixture as a REG-02 crash
-- canary. Overlaps deliberately with null_heap_alloc_malloc.iron --
-- that one is the FIX-01 rank-3 fixture, this is the REG-02
-- catalogue entry. CI integration: runs in both Debug and Release
-- via Phase 66-04's build-and-test-release job.
--
-- **Severity.** H (regression potential) -- `heap` is used by every
-- Iron program that allocates an object outside the current stack
-- frame, and a walker regression would corrupt every heap
-- constructor call on the program.

object Point {
  var x: Int
  var y: Int
}

func main() {
  val p = heap Point(3, 4)
  println("x: {p.x}")
  println("y: {p.y}")
  println("sum: {p.x + p.y}")
}
